{"questionId":"17409","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"G\">\n  <mi>G</mi>\n</math></span> is a simple, connected graph with eight vertices.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the maximum number of edges in <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"G\"> <mi>G</mi> </math></span>, given that <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"G\"> <mi>G</mi> </math></span> contains an&nbsp;Eulerian circuit.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{8 \\times 6}}{2}\"> <mfrac> <mrow> <mn>8</mn> <mo>×</mo> <mn>6</mn> </mrow> <mn>2</mn> </mfrac> </math></span> (since every vertex must be of degree 6)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" =&nbsp; 24\"> <mo>=</mo> <mn>24</mn> </math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"17409","referenceCode":"19N.3.AHL.TZ0.Hdm_4a.iii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the maximum number of edges in G , given that G contains an Eulerian circuit.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a.iii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.14—Graph theory"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}